Unlock CRM Analytics Insights on Data Cloud

Analyze your unified customer info in Data Cloud. With CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud, you can operationalize data analysis without first loading Data Cloud, prepping it, or creating live datasets.

CRM Analytics ensures that account sharing rules are automatically applied when running queries against Data Cloud. Also, our systems automatically reuse Data Cloud object names and field labels to maintain simplified data mapping between Data Cloud and the dashboard assets.

Using CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud requires the appropriate licenses, org and user account setup, and permissions assigned to user accounts.

CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud lets you create and run queries on Data Cloud records in real time. You can also build dashboard charts and tables based on these queries.

Analyze and surface customer engagement patterns from Data Cloud records without switching to Analytics Studio and creating dashboard queries. With CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud, you can now explore calculated insights, data lake objects, and data models from the data objectâ€™s record page.

To explore and draw insights from multiple related data model object (DMO) records simultaneously, join these objects in a single dashboard query. Direct Data for Data Cloud supports four types of joins on data model objects with defined relationships between them.

You can filter joined data and highlight the records that matter with conditional formatting.
